After read the add campain and disturbing anti-privacy practices of the creators (or more buyer bussines), i search to disable the popup message when you run
the spyder app on anaconda (yes allways open when you started, why? bacause they PAY $$$ to spyder dev), ok no more rant about it you can edit spyder code
to disable this shit:

locate spyder or simply go to this route:
/home/YOUR_USER/anaconda3/pkgs/spyder-4.1.5-py38_0/lib/python3.8/site-packages/spyder/config/main.py

find kite or line 525 more exactly:
'kite'

or look this image for reference:
https://i.imgur.com/EE4kRcU.png

change ALL to False... you can see this image for reference or this code too:
https://i.imgur.com/7PcwwQ7.png

code: 
            ('kite',
             {
              'enable': False,
              'call_to_action': False,
              # Enable the installation dialog
              'show_installation_dialog': False,
              'show_onboarding': False,
              'show_installation_error_message': False,
             }),
            ]
            
            
now you are free to use spyder without bloatware!!!
